        <abstract>
            <p>Is pleased GHKT goes a little way with him.</p> 
<p>Has rectified in foreign editions of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> his omission of an explanation of the failure of many forms to progress;</p> 
            <p>also has discussion of beauty in MS. Does GHKT really believe Diatomaceae, for instance, were created beautiful so that man, millions of generations later, should admire them through a microscope? CD attributes most of these structures to unknown laws of growth; useful structures are accounted for by natural selection.</p>
        </abstract>
